9.1 Cluster summary

Cluster Likely Cell Type / State
0 Homeostatic microglia
1 Homeostatic microglia (alt. subset)
2 Activated/Disease-Associated Microglia (DAM)
4 Activated/stress-response microglia
6 DAM-like / interferon-response microglia
8 Microglia with antigen-presentation signature
10 DAM / oxidative stress microglia
12 Perivascular macrophages / infiltrating myeloid cells
14 DAM-like subset / phagocytic microglia
15 T cells
17 Mixed/garbage cluster
22 Border-associated macrophages (BAMs)/activated microglia.
23 Vascular-associated cells (pericytes/endothelial)
27 Rare myeloid subset

Consider merging clusters 0 & 1. Both look like classic homeostatic microglia.

Consider merging clusters 2/10/14. All seem DAM with 2 in hypoxia- and lysosome-enriched myeloid state, 10 skewing oxidative stress (Hmox1/Nqo1) and 14 more phagocytic/clearance (Clec7a/Axl) >>> those differences should appear when we do the DE pseudobulk.
